# Rasm Documentation

**Required**: `docgen` + `style-standards` skills.

## Routing

| Change type | Skill / doc |
|-------------|-------------|
| README, ADR, changelog, architecture | `docgen` |
| Headers, lists, separators, voice | `style-standards` |
| BCL/System/package policy | `docs/system-api-map` |
| Library APIs | `docs/external-libs` |
| Test tool APIs | `docs/testing-libs` |

## Rules

- Root docs in existing paths only; remove stale or invented commands/paths
- Plans: max 1–2 screens — Context, Critical files, Approach (3–5 bullets), Verification (1–2 commands)
- No emoji; use `[X]` UPPERCASE markers per `CLAUDE.md`
- Do not duplicate `CLAUDE.md`/`AGENTS.md` content — link and distill

## Standards references

- `docs/standards/readme-standards.md`
- `docs/standards/architecture-standards.md`
- `docs/standards/code-documentation-standards.md`
- `docs/standards/voice.md`, `formatting.md`, `taxonomy.md`
